						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Slab lying in front of the temple of Bhīma.</hi></p>						

						<p>Vijayāditya—(Undated).</p>						

						<p>This inscription engraved in characters of about the <hi rend="bold">8th century A.D.,</hi> states that an individual (name lost), from Uttarāpatha built a temple (for the god Arjunīśvara), installed in it an image of Nandīśvara also, and made a gift of some land to the god Arjunīśvara. <hi rend="bold">Banniyūr</hi> (modern Bannikop) where the temple was erected, was under the administration of the <hi rend="italic">Mahājanas</hi> (of the place). </p>						

						</summary>
